    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## A.2 Reproducibility\n",
        "\n",
        "Use a fixed seed whenever simulation or randomized training is involved."
      ],
      "id": "ff3c3292"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import torch\n",
        "\n",
        "SEED = 7339\n",
        "rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\n",
        "\n",
        "torch.manual_seed(SEED)\n",
        "torch.set_num_threads(1)"
      ],
      "id": "fcd46ff5",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "In time series experiments, reproducibility means more than a seed.  It also means recording the forecasting horizon, train/test split date, scaling procedure, feature construction rule, and validation design.\n",
        "\n",
        "## A.3 Basic time-series objects\n",
        "\n",
        "A univariate time series can be stored as a `pandas.Series` with an integer index or a datetime index."
      ],
      "id": "e35768e5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "n = 120\n",
        "dates = pd.date_range(\"2026-01-01\", periods=n, freq=\"D\")\n",
        "y = pd.Series(rng.normal(size=n).cumsum(), index=dates, name=\"y\")\n",
        "\n",
        "y.head()"
      ],
      "id": "b42d6b1c",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A multivariate time series is usually stored as a `pandas.DataFrame`."
      ],
      "id": "16f1df14"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "X = pd.DataFrame({\n",
        "    \"series_a\": rng.normal(size=n).cumsum(),\n",
        "    \"series_b\": rng.normal(size=n).cumsum(),\n",
        "    \"series_c\": rng.normal(size=n).cumsum()\n",
        "}, index=dates)\n",
        "\n",
        "X.head()"
      ],
      "id": "3431fc48",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "When working with dates, always check the frequency."
      ],
      "id": "c19a9831"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "print(y.index.freq)\n",
        "print(pd.infer_freq(y.index))"
      ],
      "id": "df5a9afe",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## A.4 Plotting conventions\n",
        "\n",
        "For static plots in Python chunks, use `matplotlib`.  For book interactives, Plotly is loaded globally through `assets/header.html`; do not add another Plotly script tag inside a chapter."
      ],
      "id": "64f601f4"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| eval: false\n",
        "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 3))\n",
        "y.plot(ax=ax)\n",
        "ax.set_title(\"Time Series Plot\")\n",
        "ax.set_xlabel(\"time\")\n",
        "ax.set_ylabel(\"value\")\n",
